1 titl e, unless the person is a laser practitioner performing laser
2 hair removal under the supervision of a physician as defined in
3 paragraphs 1 through 6 of subsection A of Section 725.2 of this
4 title, a certified physician assistant, or an Advanced Practice
5 Registered Nurse certified. A laser practitioner who is not a
6 physician shall complete a laser practitioner training and education
7 program. A laser training and education program may be completed
8 internally at the laser hair removal facility or via a third party,
9 provided such third-party program is overseen by a physician. A
10 laser practitioner training and education program shall include
11 forty (40) total hours of training, which may be a combination of
12 didactic training, in-person hands-on training, and performance of
13 laser hair removal procedures.
14 C. A laser hair removal facility shall be overseen by a
15 physician; provided, that Advanced Practice Registered Nurses shall
16 be exempt from this oversight requirement, as defined in paragraphs
17 1 through 6 of subsection A of Section 725.2 of this title, a
18 certified physician assistant, or an Advanced Practice Registered
19 Nurse certified.
20 D. The overseeing physician shall:
21 1. Establish proper protocols for laser hair removal provided
22 at a facility including, but not limited to, complication
23 management. A laser practitioner shall follow all written procedure
24 protocols established and revised by the overseeing physician. Such
Req. No. 12909 Page 2

1 prot ocols shall require utilizing a physician, physician assistant,
2 or Advanced Practice Registered Nurse for complication management;
3 2. Determine the number of laser practitioners under such
4 physician's supervision; and
5 3. Review not less than ten percent (10%) of laser hair removal
6 patient records.
7 4. Every physician or physician assistant or Advanced Practice
8 Registered Nurse shall establish a relationship with patients which
9 shall include an initial evaluation, prior to treatment, that is
10 either face to face or via telemedicine that is performed by the
11 physician or physician assistant or Advanced Practice Registered
12 Nurse.
13 5. As part of the patient relationship, each physician or
14 certified physician assistant or Certified Advanced Practice
15 Registered Nurse shall create a patient chart. The chart shall
16 contain an informed consent, a treatment plan that includes risks,
17 benefits, alternatives, follow-up, and care for potential
18 complications.
19 E. A physician shall not be required to be physically present
20 or to supervise laser hair removal, but shall be available for
21 communication during the procedure, either in person or by two-way,
22 real time interactive communication.
